<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Don1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Don,</orth> subst. Spanish title before the names of noblemen: <cit><quote>D. Alphonso,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>D. Antonio,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 54</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.115" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 115</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.280" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 280</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 9</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>D. Worm, his conscience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 86</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>D. Cupid,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.182" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 182</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>Dan</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>